cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.FL

This paper deals with modelling and reasoning about dynamic memory allocation, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Additionally, the paper uses categorical semantics, which is a tool commonly used in the sub-category of category theory and homological algebra (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO, followed by cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, and cs.FL.
